description.text: I was appointed Interim Director Facilities Compliance Services which leads the Regulatory Compliance team for the enterprise. I manage the daily operations, scheduling, training, performance for the Regulatory Compliance team until the position is filled permanently.

I am the Fire Marshal for The Cleveland Clinic with responsibility for their world wide enterprise. The main focus is all things Life Safety for patients, visitors, volunteers, caregivers and contracted services.

Supervised and supported the day to day operations of the WWTP, Effluent, Boilers. Involved with many engineering projects, facilitated capital projects for Process Improvement and Cost Reduction, provided and documented all EPA and Federal regulation testing for the WWTP, did samplings for DMR permits, provided statistical support and monitored all biological and processes of the plant site, submitted permits for EPA, conducted monthly safety meetings, assisted on Green Belt projects and was a back up to the EHS Specialists and Utility Production Superintendent.

Provide assistance with environmental and safety policies, issues, documents, training, and monthly safety meetings with operators and contracters. Field tested and tracked discharges and chemicals in the plant, overseen the RCRA Waste Manifests, and audits relating to RCRA / EPA / OSHA. Helped to implement safety and environmental standards and the different safety audits needed, established a new MSDS system for the plant site, formulated a method on the HPLC and presented statistical data concerning formaldehyde levels in the Equalization/Neutralization tank. Also assisted with a new working HPLC method to test for acrylonitrile and benzenes for a production process. I was also the backup to the Waste Water Treatment Engineer.
